(134, 72, 'summary', 'Eighteen months ago, Australian-born photographer Glen Allsop was whisked away from his beach-bum lifestyle in suburban Sydney and cast out on the mean streets of NYC in a career move that’s seen him shoot some of the world’s most spectacular destinations. Working under the Christian Oth Studio banner, Glen attributes his success as a wedding photographer to his ability to encompass the roles of photojournalist, editorial shooter and party snapper all at once, while - most importantly - being a nice guy. On top of that, Glen has been quietly building his street-style portfolio since his move to the Big Apple, documenting the city’s best dressed and indulging his other big passion: luxury cars. One thing''s for sure, this guy is no one-trick pony.'),
